snippet: The blasts were said to be a backlash against the two countries for their role in a regional proxy war, and officials said no one was injured.
abstract: Car bombs explode outside the embassies of Egypt and the United Arab Emirates in Tripoli, Libya, apparently in a backlash against the two countries for their role in a regional proxy war playing out in Libya.
lead_paragraph: The blasts were said to be a backlash against the two countries for their role in a regional proxy war, and officials said no one was injured.

headline.main: Car Bombs Explode Near Egyptian and U.A.E. Embassies in Libya
